title("Boxplot of the weight of the players")

Question 9. Histogram

Make a histogram of the weight of the players. Try color green this time. The function understands the word green just fine. Give it a better title than the default. Does the distribution looks normal?

hist(df_new$weight, col="green", main = "Histogram of the weight of the players", xlab = "weight (in lbs.)")

cat("Distribution is not normal, it is right-skewed.")

Distribution is not normal, it is right-skewed.

Question 10. Scatterplot

Use ggplot, make a plot with weights vs heights of the players, color by Teams. Give it an appropriate title.

library(ggplot2)
ggplot(df_new, aes(x=weight, y=height, color=Team)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(x="weight (in lbs.)", y="height (in inches)") +
  labs(title = "Weight vs. Height point plot corresponding to teams")

Question 11. Plot by age

Make a plot with weights vs heights of the players, color by age.

ggplot(df_new, aes(x=weight, y=height)) +
  geom_point(aes(color=age)) +
  labs(x="weight (in lbs.)", y="height (in inches)") +
  labs(title = "Weight vs. Height point plot corresponding to age")
